article.headline: Evansville 65, Indiana St. 59
article.story: TERRE HAUTE, Ind. -- Shy Ely scored 24 points and Nate Garner added 21 as Evansville rallied from behind in the closing minutes for a 65-59 victory Sunday over Indiana State. Indiana State (3-11, 1-2 Missouri Valley) dominated the first half and the first five minutes of the second half before Evansville made its move. The Purple Aces (10-3, 2-1) owed their comeback largely to Ely, who scored 12 of Evansville's final 18 points. The Aces took their first lead of the game, 57-56, with 1:41 remaining on an Ely bucket off an offensive rebound. Another bucket by Ely, and two free throws by Jason Holsinger put Evansville on top, 61-58, with 21 seconds left. Indiana State, which got 16 points from Harry Marshall, wasn't able to recover. Aaron Carter added 11 points for the Sycamores, who shot 50 percent for the game. Evansville managed just 36 percent, but connected on 21 of 27 free throws -- 14 of those in the second half.
